<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-28T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="2" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/32: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-28T13:00:00-05:00">June 28,
                                    1939—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. Reference Department’s circular June 27, 7 p.m. The Haitian Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs would welcome the enactment of the resolution as the
                            Haitian Government is most sympathetic with its purposes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>